# Agentic Architecture Rules

This repository does not simulate an agent.

It prepares the repository so real coding agents can work safely and consistently.

## Core principles

- Treat agent behavior as contracts, not free-form prompts.
- Keep instructions, policies, schemas and validation scripts aligned.
- Do not add fake LLM providers.
- Do not add real external API calls without an explicit policy and approval model.
- Prefer read-only examples.
- Any write-capable behavior must be approval-gated.
- Update tests when changing manifests, policies, schemas or validation scripts.

## Layer boundaries

| Layer | Location |
| --- | --- |
| Instruction | `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.github/` |
| Capability | `.claude/agents/`, `.agents/skills/`, `agents/manifests/` |
| Policy | `policies/`, `schemas/` |
| Validation | `scripts/`, `tests/` |
| Tool demo | `mcp/` (read-only v1) |

Do not collapse layers. Policies belong in `policies/`, not ad hoc in scripts or prompts.

## Before finishing substantive changes

```powershell
python scripts/validate_agentic_repo.py
pytest -q
```
